    {
      "overview_item_type": "essential_ideas",
      "overview_item_content_type": "html",
      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "You can represent simple interest using a linear function and compound interest using an exponential function.",
          "An exponential growth function is of the form <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mi>x</mi></msup></math>, where <math><mi>r</mi></math> is the rate of growth.",
          "An exponential decay function is of the form <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>–</mo><mi>r</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mi>x</mi></msup></math>, where <math><mi>r</mi></math> is the rate of decay."
        ]
      }
    },
